@startuml fig-vlsm-allocation
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false

title VLSM Allocation Process (IPv4)

start

:Collect host requirements\nfor all subnets;

:Sort requirements in\n**descending** order;

:Select the starting\naddress block (e.g. 10.0.0.0/24);

repeat
    :Take the largest remaining\nrequirement;

    :Find the smallest prefix\nthat fits (round up to\nnext power of two + 2);

    :Allocate from the current\nfree position;

    :Record: network address,\nbroadcast, host range;

    :Advance pointer past\nallocated block;

repeat while (More subnets needed?) is (yes)
->no;

:Verify no overlaps\nand all requirements met;

stop

legend right
  Example: 10.0.0.0/24
  100 hosts → /25 (10.0.0.0)
  50 hosts  → /26 (10.0.0.128)
  10 hosts  → /28 (10.0.0.192)
  2 hosts   → /30 (10.0.0.208)
  Always allocate largest first.
endlegend
@enduml
